Korean Roasted Vegetables with Pickled Daikon

Daikon:
1/2 large (8oz) daikon, peeled, quartered lengthwise and thinly sliced
1 tbsp salt
1/2 c rice vinegar
1/2 sugar
1/2 c water
1/2 tsp tumeric

In a small bowl toss the daikon with the salt. Transfer to a colander and let drain for 45 min. Rinse the daikon well with cool water and transfer to a glass jar. In as small pot, bring the rice vinegar, sugar, water, and tumeric to a boil. Pour over the daikon to cover and let cool completely. Can be made up to 1 week in advance.

Veggies:
2 tbsp honey
2 tbsp shoyu
2 tbsp vegetable oil
1 tsp Korean red pepper flakes
1 tsp gochujang
1 large (1 lb) daikon, halved and cut into 1/4" slices
8 small (8 oz) rainbow carrots, halved
6 medium (8oz) easter egg radishes, quartered
3 garlic cloves, minced
6" stalk lemongrass, tough outer leaves discarded, inner core thinly sliced
kosher salt to taste
pickled daikon for garnish
thinly sliced scallions for garnish

Preheat the oven to 450F and likne a baking sheet with foil. In a large bowl, whisk together the honey, shoyu, oil, pepper flakes, and gochujang. Add the daikon, carrots, radishes, garlic, and lemon grass, and toss to coat. Season with salt. Spread the vegetables onto the prepared baking sheet in an even layer. Roast, turning occasionally, until tender and caramelized, 30 min. Transfer to a platter and top with 1/2 c pickled daikon and sliced scallions. Serve immediately with remaining pickled daikon on the side.
